What is social work; development and influences for social work; social work in Estonia; the main concepts; interacation between theory and practice; the main contemporary ideas, theories and practice models; knowledge based practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with understanding of social work as a whole profession that consists of academic knowledge and practical work; reinforce the key concepts introduced in the lessons. This course also helps to master other subjects of social work is a prerequisite for writing the Bachelor thesis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: 1)has a consistent overview of social work theory and its development history; the concept of social work; 2)knows the main theories and practice models of social work; 3)makes connections between theory and practice by analyzing; 4)resolves different cases and analyzes contexts by using theory and approach of social work; 5)analyzes himself as a learner of social work theory and models.
